  "voiceover": "Muslims often say Jesus was a Muslim. He wasn't — and the claim trades on two meanings of one word. \"Muslim\" can mean simply \"one who submits to God.\" But the religion of Islam is something specific: defined by Muhammad and the Quran — the seventh century, six hundred years after Jesus. Jesus was a first-century Jew who kept the Torah and never heard of Muhammad. And the Jesus of history did what no Muslim ever could: he forgave sins in his own name, accepted worship, and claimed to share the Father's own glory — which, on Islam's own terms, is shirk, impossible for a mere prophet. So either we trust the Gospels — and Jesus was no Muslim — or we throw them out, and there's no \"Muslim Jesus\" left at all. Yes, Jesus submitted to the Father, perfectly — but as God the Son, who became human to save us. Not a Muslim. The Lord.",
